                                    CommSer
                                    =======


CommSer is a littel program to communicate with a device (f. e. serial.device)
It understands four arguments:

-sSendString   (SendString will be send to the device.)
                example: -sAT&V
                         -sATI3

-dDeviceName   (DeviceName is the name of the used device)
                example: -dserial.device
                         -dserlog.device

-uUnit         (Unit is the unitnumber)
                example: -u0
                         -u1

-wWaitTicks    (WaitTicks is number of of ticks CommSer will wait for an
                answer)
                example: -w20
                         -w100

If no arguments are given, SendString is "AT" and
                           DeviceName is "serial.device".
                           Unit       is "0"
                           WaitTicks  is "0"

If you have any questions or notes feel free to contact me.

